{
  "texts": [
    "Common criteria include the lowest p-value in a t-test for the coefficient, the largest increase in R 2, or a significant decrease in the Akaike Information Criterion (AIC) or Bayesian Information Criterion (BIC). 3.",
    "Model Evaluation After adding the new variable, evaluate the model to ensure it significantly improves the model's performance.",
    "This can involve checking for statistical significance, improvements in goodness-of-fit measures, or cross-validation performance. 4.",
    "Iteration Repeat the variable selection and model evaluation steps, adding one variable at a time, until no further significant improvements can be made to the model.",
    "The result is a model that includes a subset of the available variables that best explain the variation in the response variable, based on the criteria used for variable selection."
  ]
}